# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Check if the linked list is empty or has only one node. If so, return the head of the linked list. 

Otherwise, create a pointer next to the second node in the linked list.

Set the next pointer of the first node to the result of recursively calling swapPairs on the third node (if it exists) and beyond.

Set the next pointer of the next node to the first node.
Return the next node as the new head of the linked list.
Done !!!!
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(N)
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
