# Intuition
At every node , we have two possible actions 
1. At this node, we decide to join the paths from left and right , which means we are trying to form our answer from this node.
2. Find the maximum path from left and right , so that it can be used by the ancestor nodes to perform action 1.

# Approach
1. We will just do a postorder traversal
2. At each node, we maximise the answer by adding maximum in left and right
3. At the same time we find the maximum path, from left and right
4. If the pathsum becomes less than 0, we should drop that path

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity:O(h) h=height of tree 
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

